<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB09196</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROFESSIONALIZING THE PRACTICE OF THE PARALEGAL PROFESSION IN THE PHILIPPINES, AND APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Intends to give Filipinos who have been practicing paralegal work the necessary recognition and government
assistance to develop the profession.

Defines Paralegal profession as government-sanctioned performance of specifically delegated substantive legal
work for which a lawyer is responsible, including but not limited to legal research, drafting of simple 
legal documents, liaising with judicial and quasi-judicial bodies, etc. and for which a license to practice
law is not required under prevailing rules and regulations.

Provides for the creation of the Professional Regulatory Board of Paralegals; licensure examination requirement, 
qualifications and rating; issuance of the certificate of registration and professional license; roster of paralegals
in good standing; prohibition on the practice and Continuing Professional Development (CPD) Program of paralegal.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ZUBIRI, MANUEL F., BRAVO, ANTHONY M., Ph.D., SARMIENTO, CESAR V., BERTIZ, ANICETO &quot;JOHN&quot; III D.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-05-22</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON CIVIL SERVICE AND PROFESSIONAL REGULATION ON 2019-05-27</td></tr></table>